"title": "6227: regret",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6227: regret",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Deep feelings of sorrow arising from past events now seen as sins, mistakes or misfortunes. It can either lead to true repentance or destructive bitterness.</p>\n<h2>Examples and expressions of regret</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam26:21\">1SA 26:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:33-Gen27:35\">GEN 27:33–27:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num12:10-Num12:12\">NUM 12:10–12:12</a> <em>Aaron and Miriam when they had spoken against Moses</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:1-Num14:2\">NUM 14:1–14:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg11:34-Judg11:35\">JDG 11:34–11:35</a> <em>Jephthah when he returned home from fighting the Ammonites</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:10\">2SA 24:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr21:8\">1CH 21:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:14\">2SA 24:14</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr21:13\">1CH 21:13</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:27\">1KI 21:27</a> <em>Ahab after he murdered Naboth and seized his vineyard</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:14\">DAN 6:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:75\">MAT 26:75</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:72\">MRK 14:72</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:61-Luke22:62\">LUK 22:61–22:62</a> <em>Peter when he disowned Jesus Christ</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:3-Matt27:4\">MAT 27:3–27:4</a> <em>Judas after betraying Jesus Christ</em></p>\n<h2>Divine expressions of regret</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:6\">GEN 6:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:10-1Sam15:11\">1SA 15:10–15:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:35\">1SA 15:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:16\">2SA 24:16</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr21:15\">1CH 21:15</a></p>\n<h2>Actions which may lead to regret</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov5:11-Prov5:14\">PRO 5:11–5:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:9-1Tim6:10\">1TI 6:9–6:10</a></p>\n<h2>The bitterness of vain regrets</h2>\n<h3>There is no remedy for bitter regrets</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:16-Heb12:17\">HEB 12:16–12:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:41\">GEN 27:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam18:33\">2SA 18:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:17\">PRO 28:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek7:16-Ezek7:18\">EZK 7:16–7:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:24-Luke13:28\">LUK 13:24–13:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:7\">REV 1:7</a></p>\n<h3>The unending remorse of the lost</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan12:2\">DAN 12:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:24\">ISA 66:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:12\">MAT 8:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:30\">MAT 25:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:47-Mark9:48\">MRK 9:47–9:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:22-Luke16:23\">LUK 16:22–16:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:11\">REV 14:11</a></p>\n<h2>Regret is an element of true repentance</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor7:8-2Cor7:10\">2CO 7:8–7:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:39-Num14:40\">NUM 14:39–14:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:13-2Sam12:17\">2SA 12:13–12:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs22:18-2Kgs22:20\">2KI 22:18–22:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:26-2Chr34:28\">2CH 34:26–34:28</a> <em>Josiah's response on finding the Book of the Law</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:1\">EZR 10:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:6\">EZR 10:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps38:2-Ps38:8\">PSA 38:2–38:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:3\">PSA 51:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:21-Jer3:25\">JER 3:21–3:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:12\">JOL 2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:6-Jonah3:9\">JON 3:6–3:9</a> <em>the repentance of Nineveh</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:4\">MAT 5:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:17-Luke15:19\">LUK 15:17–15:19</a> <em>the prodigal son</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:37\">ACT 2:37</a></p>\n<h2>Absence of regret</h2>\n<h3>Sinning without shame</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:15\">JER 6:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:5\">ZEP 3:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:1-1Cor5:2\">1CO 5:1–5:2</a></p>\n<h3>When the wicked die</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr21:20\">2CH 21:20</a></p>\n<h3>At the end of life</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:5\">2SA 23:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:6-2Tim4:8\">2TI 4:6–4:8</a></p>\n<h3>In God's new creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:17-Isa65:19\">ISA 65:17–65:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:10\">ISA 35:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:4\">REV 21:4</a></p>",
